project.name: BudgetWise Pro
project.notes: This game is designed for students interested in learning about making decisions and managing your money properly! With real life circumstances like going to college, this game stimulates real life circumstances and environments in order to normalize the concept of decision making. Complete student code blanks to create a properly functioning game and then play away!

block.l: This is the apartment you found for 1500 to buy, or 500 dollars to rent. Do you want to rent or buy?
Good choice! Renting is a lot cheaper and offers a lot more flexibility
Probably not a good idea to start to buy a house immedeately after graduating, however there are benefits.
After a long day you come back home and see you have run out of food. Do you want to eat out or buy groceries?
Eating out can be very expensive and should only be done a few times
Make sure you say "eat out" or "buy groceries"
Buying groceries can get you multiple meals which can save you a lot of money longterm
You just realized that you did not have insurance for your apartment. Do you want insurance? (yes or no)
Insurance is very important, they insure that all of are belongings can easily be replaced when an accident happens.
Insurance is actually very important, and should always be your first priority with money.
